Cattle futures prices were also supported yesterday by signs that supermarket chains are making plans to increase their promotions concerning beef. 

GRAINS AND SOYBEANS: The prices of most soybean and soybean-meal futures contracts rose amid rumors that the Soviet Union is interested in buying from the U.S. or South America about 250,000 metric tons of soybeans and as many as 400,000 metric tons of soybean meal.
