Czechoslovakia's premier said he supports broad political and economic restructuring, but ruled out any dialogue between Prague's Communist government and independent human-rights or dissident groups.
Ladislav Adamec, ending a two-day visit to Austria, pledged changes in Czechoslovakia, including freer travel to the West. 

Died: Mary McCarthy, 77, novelist and literary critic, in New York City, of cancer. . . . Marion Harper, 73, founder and ex-chief executive of Interpublic Group of Cos., in Oklahoma City, of a heart attack. 

Sotheby's Holdings Inc., the parent of the auction house Sotheby's, said its net loss for the seasonally slow third quarter narrowed from a year earlier on a leap in operating revenue. 

The New York-based company reported a third-quarter net loss of $5.1 million, or 10 cents a share, compared with a year-earlier net loss of $6.2 million, or 12 cents a share.
